repository-code: "https://github.com/Tej-Katika/amr-sentinel"
url: "https://github.com/Tej-Katika/amr-sentinel"
abstract: >-
  AMR Sentinel is an open-source, event-driven antimicrobial resistance (AMR)
  surveillance and clinical stewardship platform. It ingests antimicrobial
  susceptibility test data from hospital microbiology labs in real time,
  classifies isolates against EUCAST and CLSI breakpoints, runs streaming
  outbreak detection (CUSUM and BOCPD), and exposes an LLM-assisted clinical
  stewardship interface for empiric therapy recommendations grounded in local
  resistance patterns. The platform is designed as parameterized infrastructure
  for catchment-region researchers and stewardship teams to refine with local
  breakpoints, ward-mix, and antibiotic-cost data.
